	        		        	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">PGM:Problem Set: MAP Inference and Week 4 Review</h1>
				<div id="bodyContent">
		            <h3 id="siteSub">From Coursera</h3>
		            <div id="contentSub"></div>
		            		            		            					<!-- start content -->
					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>The when running the MAP inference algorithm, two clusters $$C&#95;i$$ and $$C&#95;j$$ joined by sepset $$S&#95;{i,j}$$ are said to be "max-calibrated" if</p>
<p>$$\max&#95;{C&#95;i - S&#95;{i,j}} \beta&#95;i = \max&#95;{C&#95;j - S&#95;{i,j}} \beta&#95;j $$.  </p>
<p>Above </p>
<p>$$ \beta&#95;j = \theta&#95;{C&#95;j} + \sum&#95;k \lambda&#95;{k\rightarrow j}$$ </p>
<p>where $$\theta&#95;{C&#95;j}$$ is the logarithm of the product of the factors assigned to cluster $$j$$ and $$\lambda&#95;{k\rightarrow j}$$ is the message passed from cluster $$k$$ to cluster $$j$$.</p>
<p>See the second to last slide titled "Max-Sum BP at Convergence" of the "MAP Exact Inference" lecture or Chapter 13.3.1 in Koller and Friedman.</p>

